Text.string: Gahh. How am I supposed to profit off this war-torn—||I mean, heh, sell premium weapons to heroic Vault Hunters such as yourself! Let's fix my vending machine! And by that I mean: you fix it!

Damn psychos. Always scavenging to make their buzz-axes and meat bicycles. You'll need to replace that circuit with something. Hmm. You know, some skags are chock-full of electricity. Get me one of their spines!
And, as an added thank you for dishing out some vengeance on those filthy bandits, let me open up my secret stash for you. Who says payback doesn't pay, eh?
Ah, you found a human spine. You'll fit right in on Pandora, heh-heh-heh. Give it a try.
Now find one of those shock skags and get their spine. That should work. For real this time.
You've already got a shock skag spine. Try that. It will work much better, I promise.
There's one of those shock skags now! Get its spine!
Go on, pick it up! Hope you don't mind handling viscera!
Oh, and if you're feeling extra gruesome, you could also try getting a human spine from one of those filthy bandits! That could work.
Gahahaha! That bandit spine's not actually gonna work, gaha. I just wanted some payback because those bastards broke my machine! Still, I appreciate your dedication to capitalism!
Ah, very good! Bring it back to the machine. And be quick about it!
Well done, Vault Hunter! You now have access to my vast array of murderous wares in a new convenient location.
Better get used to doing things like this if you want to survive on Pandora!
Here, let me open up my secret stash for you. Who says payback doesn't pay, eh?
